e 151-163 in `entire-agent-roger-roger/main.go`):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"protocol_version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"roger-roger\\\",\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"Roger Roger Agent\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Roger Roger - just a test agent\\\",\\n  \\\"protected_dirs\\\": [\\\".roger-roger\\\"],\\n  \\\"hook_names\\\": [\\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\", \\\"stop\\\", \\\"user-prompt-submit\\\"],\\n  \\\"capabilities\\\": {\\n    \\\"hooks\\\": true,\\n    \\\"transcript_analyzer\\\": true,\\n    \\\"hook_response_writer\\\": true\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Protected Directories:**\\n- `.roger-roger` — Excluded from git operations during rewind\\n\\n### 4. Interaction with Entire CLI\\n\\n**Lifecycle Hooks (from roger-roger/main.go, lines 26-45):**\\n\\nRoger-roger fires hooks at key moments by calling `entire hooks roger-roger <hookName>`:\\n\\n| Hook | Payload | When Fired |\\n|------|---------|-----------|\\n| `session-start` | `{session_id, transcript_path}` | Agent REPL starts |\\n| `user-prompt-submit` | `{session_id, transcript_path, prompt}` | User enters prompt |\\n| `stop` | `{session_id, transcript_path}` | Agent finishes responding |\\n| `session-end` | `{session_id, transcript_path}` | User exits REPL |\\n\\n**Hook Invocation Pattern** (line 99):\\n```go\\ncmd := exec.Command(\\\"entire\\\", \\\"hooks\\\", \\\"roger-roger\\\", hookName)\\ncmd.Stdin = bytes.NewReader(data)  // JSON payload\\n```\\n\\nThe CLI processes these hooks through the manual-commit strategy, creating shadow branch checkpoints and managing session state.\\n\\n### 5. Hooks, Lifecycle Events & Protocol Implementation\\n\\n**Implemented Subcommands** (entire-agent-roger-roger/main.go, lines 24-68):\\n\\n**Always-Required:**\\n- `info` — Metadata declaration\\n- `detect` — Returns `{\\\"present\\\": false}` (not auto-detected)\\n- `get-session-id`, `get-session-dir`, `resolve-session-file` — Session location\\n- `read-session`, `write-session` — Session persistence\\n- `read-tra