gent.AgentSession) error {\\n   141→\\tif session == nil {\\n   142→\\t\\treturn errors.New(\\\"session is nil\\\")\\n   143→\\t}\\n   144→\\n   145→\\t// Verify this session belongs to Claude Code\\n   146→\\tif session.AgentName != \\\"\\\" && session.AgentName != c.Name() {\\n   147→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"session belongs to agent %q, not %q\\\", session.AgentName, c.Name())\\n   148→\\t}\\n   149→\\n   150→\\tif session.SessionRef == \\\"\\\" {\"}]},\"uuid\":\"c5c0926a-76e0-46e1-a727-b89286935c8d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T08:48:26.557Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"adb21441cd21363f7\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01GsUghYiGvsH78ajkViyFFd\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01VqhZ6YnLWjw7rSK8mNWUKw\",\"uuid\":\"8d9abac0-60b9-4841-8d96-5094035f4309\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T08:48:26.564Z\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"1389d7d7-e618-4144-8a22-a19bc90b3c54\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"delegated-fluttering-corbato\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8d9abac0-60b9-4841-8d96-5094035f4309\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Agent\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01VqhZ6YnLWjw7rSK8mNWUKw\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01VqhZ6YnLWjw7rSK8mNWUKw\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-16T08:49:17.827Z\",\"uuid\":\"207e70b8-0a63-4e3c-b58d-ecae5b44b5e6\",\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"1389d7d7-e618-4144-8a22-a19bc90b3c54\",\"version\":\"2.1.76\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"delegated-fluttering-corbato\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"bf33285c-dfb7-4121-8d45-1ef3b1e30028\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"promptId\":\"b30e8129-086b-45ef-82ad-323be3e0da1c\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01VqhZ6YnLWjw7rSK8mNWUKw\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary document with all the key information:\\n\\n## Summary: E2E Test Infrastructure Exploration\\n\\nBased on my thorough exploration of the E2E test infrastructure, here's a comprehensive overview:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **1. E2E Test Structure (`e2e/` directory)**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/`\\n\\n**Key Subdirectories:**\\n- **`agents/`** - Agent abstraction layer (8 agents implemented: Claude Code, Gemini, OpenCode, Cursor, Copilot CLI, Factory AI Droid, Vogon, and base agent interface)\\n- **`bootstrap/`** - CI pre-test setup (auth config, warmup routines)\\n- **`tests/`** - Blessed test files run by CI (single session, multi-session, rewind, checkpoints, etc.)\\n- **`testutil/`** - Repo setup, assertions, artifact capture helpers\\n- **`entire/`** - CLI wrapper for running `entire` commands in tests\\n- **`vogon/`** - Standalone Vogon binary for E2E canary tests (deterministic, no API calls)\\n\\n**Test Build Tag:** All E2E tests use `//go:build e2e` and are in `e2e/tests/`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **2. E2E Test README (`e2e/README.md`)**\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n- Tests make real API calls and cost money — only run when explicitly requested\\n- CI workflows:\\n  - `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` - Full suite on main (all agents in matrix)\\n  - `.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml` - Manual dispatch for single test debugging\\n- Environment variables:\\n  - `E2E_AGENT` - Filter by agent name (claude-code, gemini-cli, opencode, cursor-cli, copilot-cli, vogon)\\n  - `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN` - Pre-built binary path (default: builds from source)\\n  - `E2E_TIMEOUT` - Per-prompt timeout (default: 2m)\\n  - `E2E_KEEP_REPOS` - Preserve temp repos for debugging\\n  - `E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR` - Override artifact output directory\\n- Artifacts captured to `e2e/artifacts/<timestamp>`:\\n  - `console.log` - Full operation transcript\\n  - `git-log.txt`, `git-tree.txt` - Repo state\\n  - `entire-logs/` - Internal CLI logs\\n  - `checkpoint-metadata/` - Checkpoint data\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **3. How Existing E2E Tests Work**\\n\\n**Test Pattern:**\\n```go\\nfunc TestExample(t *testing.T) {\\n    testutil.ForEachAgent(t, 2*time.Minute, func(t *testing.T, s *testutil.RepoState, ctx context.Context) {\\n        // Run prompt\\n        _, err := s.RunPrompt(t, ctx, \\\"create a file at docs/test.md with a paragraph\\\")\\n        \\n        // Make assertions\\n        testutil.AssertFileExists(t, s.Dir, \\\"docs/*.md\\\")\\n        testutil.WaitForCheckpoint(t, s, 15*time.Second)\\n        testutil.AssertCheckpointAdvanced(t, s)\\n    })\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key Helpers (from `testutil` package):**\\n- `ForEachAgent()` - Runs test for each registered agent, handles repo setup, concurrency gating, timeouts, and scenario restart on transient errors\\n- `SetupRepo()` - Creates fresh git repo, seeds with initial commit, runs `entire enable`\\n- `RepoState` - Holds test state: agent, dir, artifact dir, console log, HEAD snapshot\\n- `s.RunPrompt()` - Sends prompt to agent, captures output, logs to console.log\\n- `s.Git()` - Runs git commands, logs to console.log\\n- Assertions: `AssertFileExists()`, `WaitForCheckpoint()`, `AssertCheckpointAdvanced()`, `AssertHasCheckpointTrailer()`, `AssertCheckpointExists()`, `GetCheckpointTrailer()`, `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom()`, etc.\\n\\n**Example Tests:**\\n- `TestHumanOnlyChangesAndCommits` - Human commits without agent (no checkpoint)\\n- `TestSingleSessionManualCommit` - Agent creates file, human commits manually\\n- `TestSingleSessionAgentCommitInTurn` - Agent creates and commits in one prompt\\n- `TestMultiSessionConcurrent` - Two sessions in same dir (concurrent checkpoints)\\n- `TestRewindMultipleCheckpoints` - Rewind to earlier checkpoint\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **4. Vogon Agent - E2E Canary**\\n\\n**Two Components:**\\n\\n#### **A. Vogon Binary (`e2e/vogon/main.go`)**\\n- **Purpose:** Deterministic fake agent for CI canary tests (no API calls, no cost)\\n- **Headless mode:** `vogon -p \\\"<prompt>\\\"` - Single turn\\n- **Interactive mode:** `vogon` - Multi-turn with tmux\\n- **Hooks:** Fires lifecycle hooks via `entire hooks vogon <verb>`:\\n  - `session-start`, `session-end`, `user-prompt-submit`, `stop`\\n- **Prompt parsing:** Regex-based (hardcoded regexes for file operations):\\n  - Create: `create a [markdown|text] file [at|called] <path>`\\n  - Modify: `modify [the] [file] [at] <path>`\\n  - Delete: `delete [the] [file] [at] <path>`\\n  - Commit: `commit` (unless `do not commit` in prompt)\\n  - Special: \\\"commit each file separately\\\" → interleave commits with creates\\n  - Numbered steps: `(1) create file A. (2) create file B. (3) commit.`\\n- **File operations:** Create, modify (append), delete files\\n- **Git operations:** `git add`, `git commit` with \\\"Vogon agent commit\\\" message\\n- **Transcript:** JSONL format saved to `~/.vogon/sessions/<session-id>.jsonl`\\n- **Important:** When changing E2E test prompt wording, Vogon's hardcoded regexes may not match new phrasing — must run `mise run test:e2e:canary` and fix Vogon if tests fail\\n\\n#### **B. Vogon Agent in CLI (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/vogon/`)**\\n- **Registration:** Auto-registered as `agent.AgentNameVogon` (registry key: \\\"vogon\\\")\\n- **Type:** `agent.AgentTypeVogon` (\\\"Vogon Agent\\\")\\n- **Test-only:** Implements `agent.TestOnly` interface (excluded from `entire enable` UI)\\n- **Implements:** `Agent` + `HookSupport` + `HookResponseWriter`\\n- **Protected dirs:** `.vogon`\\n- **Never auto-detected** (`DetectPresence()` returns false)\\n- **Hook parsing:**\\n  - `session-start` → `SessionStart` event\\n  - `user-prompt-submit` → `TurnStart` event + prompt text\\n  - `stop` → `TurnEnd` event\\n  - `session-end` → `SessionEnd` event\\n- **Transcript storage:** Raw JSONL files (same format as Claude Code)\\n- **Session lifecycle:** Minimal implementation (test-only agent