ession-id>.jsonl`\\n- **Protected dirs:** `[\\\".claude\\\"]`\\n- **Auto-detect:** Checks for `.claude` directory or `.claude/settings.json`\\n- **Hooks:** Registers 4 hooks (session-start, session-end, user-prompt-submit, stop)\\n- **Transcript format:** JSONL (line-based), each line is a message\\n- **File extraction:** Parses messages with `tool_name: \\\"Write\\\"` or `\\\"Edit\\\"`\\n- **Prompt extraction:** Parses user messages from JSONL\\n- **Token calculation:** Delegates to `TranscriptCalculateTokens` helper\\n- **Text generation:** Calls `claude --print` for metadata generation\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **9. E2E Test Architecture in E2E Agents Package**\\n\\n**Agent Interface (`e2e/agents/agent.go`):**\\n```go\\ntype Agent interface {\\n    Name() string                    // Registry key (e.g., \\\"vogon\\\")\\n    Binary() string                  // CLI binary name (e.g., \\\"vogon\\\")\\n    EntireAgent() string             // Value for `entire enable` (e.g., \\\"vogon\\\")\\n    PromptPattern() string           // Regex to detect prompt readiness\\n    TimeoutMultiplier() float64      // Scale timeouts (Gemini = 2.0, Vogon = 0.5)\\n    RunPrompt(ctx, dir, prompt, opts...) Output  // Non-interactive prompt\\n    StartSession(ctx, dir) Session   // Interactive session (tmux)\\n    Bootstrap() error                // One-time CI setup\\n    IsTransientError(out, err) bool  // Is error worth retrying?\\n}\\n\\ntype Session interface {\\n    Send(input) error                // Send prompt + wait for echo\\n    WaitFor(pattern, timeout) string // Poll for regex pattern\\n    Capture() string                 // Current pane content\\n    Close() error                    // Kill session\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Agent Implementations:**\\n- `claudecode` - Real Claude Code agent via `claude` CLI\\n- `gemini` - Real Gemini CLI agent via `gemini` CLI\\n- `opencode` - Real OpenCode agent via `opencode` CLI\\n- `cursor` - Real Cursor agent via `cursor` CLI\\n- `copilot-cli` - Real Copilot CLI agent via `copilot` CLI\\n- `factoryai-droid` - Factory AI Droid (Gemini variant)\\n- `vogon` - Deterministic fake agent (E2E canary)\\n\\n**Concurrency Control:**\\n- `RegisterGate(name, defaultMax)` - Set max concurrent tests (overridable via `E2E_CONCURRENT_TEST_LIMIT`)\\n- `AcquireSlot(ctx, agent)` - Wait for available slot\\n- `ReleaseSlot(agent)` - Free slot after test\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **10. Key Files Summary**\\n\\n**Agent Interface & Registry:**\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` - Core interfaces\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` - Registration + discovery\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/types.go` - Type definitions\\n\\n**External Agents:**\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go` - External agent wrapper\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/types.go` - Protocol types\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/discovery.go` - Binary discovery via PATH\\n\\n**Vogon (CLI Agent):**\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/vogon/vogon.go` - Agent implementation\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/vogon/hooks.go` - Hook handling\\n\\n**Vogon (Binary):**\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/vogon/main.go` - Standalone binary (444 lines)\\n\\n**E2E Test Infrastructure:**\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/README.md` - Documentation\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/agents/agent.go` - E2E agent interface\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/agents/vogon.go` - E2E Vogon adapter\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/agents/tmux.go` - tmux session manager\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/testutil/repo.go` - Repo setup + ForEachAgent\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/testutil/assertions.go` - Test assertions\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/testutil/artifacts.go` - Artifact capture\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/tests/main_test.go` - TestMain setup\\n- `/Users/nodo/work/cli/e2e/tests/single_session_test.go` - Example tests\\n\\n---\\n\\nThis comprehensive ex